# pnpm's strict-by-default module layout doesn't expose transitive deps
# at the top of node_modules. `vite/client` (referenced from tsconfig's
# `types` array for `import.meta.glob` + CSS module declarations) is
# pulled in transitively via wxt + @sveltejs/vite-plugin-svelte, so
# it's not resolvable from the project root by default — svelte-check
# then fails with "Property 'glob' does not exist on type 'ImportMeta'".
#
# Hoisting the transitive `vite` (and anything named `vite-*`) to the
# top of node_modules fixes the type resolution without pulling in a
# SECOND copy of vite as a direct dep (which would mismatch wxt's
# pinned version and break tsc in a different way).
public-hoist-pattern[]=vite
public-hoist-pattern[]=vite-*
